<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298336>
    dc:description "Fig. 91. Tegula. A. Lasioglossum (D.) hunteri (Crawford, 1932), ♀, enlarged, reaching scutellum, with concave inner posterior margin. B. L. (D.) clematisellum (Cockerell, 1904), ♀, ovoid and not reaching scutellum. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298336/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298338>
    dc:description "Fig. 92. Head and mesonotum. A. Lasioglossum (D.) vierecki (Crawford, 1904), ♀, with thickly plumose hair short and scale-like. B. L. (D.) cembrilacus sp. nov., ♀, with thickly plumose hair long. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298338/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298282>
    dc:description "Fig. 67. Lasioglossum (D.) pallidellum (Ellis, 1914), red morph, ♀. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Face. D. Propodeum. E. Metasoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298282/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298340>
    dc:description "Fig. 93. Mesoscutum. A. Lasioglossum (D.) tessellatosum sp. nov., ♀, with strong microsculpture and sparse punctures. B. L. (D.) droegei Gibbs, 2009, ♂, with strong microsculpture and dense punctures. C. L. (D.) cactorum sp. nov., ♀, shiny and sparsely punctate. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298340/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298342>
    dc:description "Fig. 94. Variation in frons punctation. A. Lasioglossum (D.) tessellatosum sp. nov., ♀, reticulatepunctate to ruguloso-punctate with crowded punctures. B. L. (D.) meteorum sp. nov., ♀, fine and dense but distinctly separated punctures. C. L. (D.) julipile sp. nov., ♀, moderately sparsely punctate. D. L. (D.) perditum sp. nov., ♀, very sparsely punctate. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298342/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298344>
    dc:description "Fig. 95. T1 anterior face. A. Lasioglossum (D.) kunzei (Cockerell, 1898), ♀, shiny with weak and worn acarinarial fan. B. L. (D.) argammon sp. nov., ♀, weakly coriarious with sparse acarinarial fan. C. L. (D.) rufornatum sp. nov., ♀, strongly coriarious with dense and well-developed acarinarial fan. Arrows point to areas where microsculpture is most easily visible. Scale bar is 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298344/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298346>
    dc:description "Fig. 96. T1 anterior face. A. Lasioglossum (D.) testaceum (Robertson, 1897), ♀, acarinarial fan absent with erect hairs throughout. B. L. (D.) clastipedion sp. nov., ♀, acarinarial fan present but weak, with erect hairs restricted to lateral margins. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298346/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298348>
    dc:description "Fig. 97. T1–3. A. Lasioglossum (D.) cactorum sp. nov., ♀, with very narrow and abruptly downcurved apical rims and dense apical hair fringes. B. L. (D.) miltolepoides sp. nov., ♀, with broad, flat, slightly depressed apical rims and sparse apical hair fringes. Arrows point to approximate lengthwise center of apical rims. Scale bar: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298348/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298350>
    dc:description "Fig. 98. Propodeum. A. Lasioglossum (D.) testaceum (Robertson, 1897), ♀, with strong oblique carina (arrow). B. L. (D.) minckleyi sp. nov., ♀, without oblique carina. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298350/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298354>
    dc:description "Fig. 99. Middle tibial spurs. A. Minutely serrate. B. Finely pectinate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298354/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298356>
    dc:description "Fig. 100. Forewings. A. Lasioglossum (D.) pallidellum (Ellis, 1914), ♂, with white hair, pale veins, and hyaline membrane. B. L. (D.) decorum sp. nov., ♀, with dark hair, dark veins, and lightly infuscated membrane. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298356/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298358>
    dc:description "Fig. 101. Supraclypeal area. A. Lasioglossum (D.) arenisaltans sp. nov., ♀, mostly tessellate. B. L. (D.) mesillense (Cockerell, 1898), ♀, mostly shiny. Scale bar: 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298358/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298360>
    dc:description "Fig. 102. Postgena.A. Lasioglossum (D.) pictum (Crawford, 1902), ♀, dull and lineate. B. L. (D.) lilianae sp. nov., ♀, shiny. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298360/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298300>
    dc:description "Fig. 75. Lasioglossum (D.) rufornatum sp. nov., ♀. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Face. D. Propodeum and metasoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298300/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298155>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Lasioglossum (D.) arenisaltans sp. nov., ♀. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Face. C. Lateral habitus. D. Propodeum. E. Metasoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298155/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298215>
    dc:description "Fig. 36. Lasioglossum (D.) eophilus (Ellis, 1914), ♀. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Face. D. Propodeum. E. Metasoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298215/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298362>
    dc:description "Fig. 103. Ocelli. A. Lasioglossum (D.) eophilus (Ellis, 1914), ♀, slightly enlarged and separated by less than two thirds of one ocellar diameter. B. L. (D.) miltolepoides sp. nov., ♀, normal size, separated by more than two thirds of one ocellar diameter. Scale bar: 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298362/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298161>
    dc:description "Fig. 11. Lasioglossum (D.) argammon sp. nov., holotype, ♀. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Propodeum. D. Face. E. Metasoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298161/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298364>
    dc:description "Fig. 104. Propodeum. A. Lasioglossum (D.) pallidellum (Ellis, 1914), ♀, with metapostnotal rugae not reaching the posterior margin. B. L. (D.) clastipedion sp. nov., ♀, with metapostnotal rugae reaching the posterior margin. Scale bar: 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298364/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298366>
    dc:description "Fig. 105. Dark spiracular spots (arrows) on the metasoma. A. Lasioglossum (D.) pictum (Crawford, 1902), ♀, present on T2–4. B. L. (D.) meteorum sp. nov., ♀, present on T3–4 only. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298366/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298247>
    dc:description "Fig. 52. Lasioglossum (D.) lilianae sp. nov., ♀. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Face. D. Propodeum and metasoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4298247/files/figure.png" ;
